positive.review:
Palia is the definition of 'Cozy', with no concept of threats or combat mechanics (except hunting animals with a bow as a skill). A beautiful and relaxing Co-op game with enough content to last many hours (at least a couple hundred) and it is not even in its final state. Plus, it's completely FREE (you can only pay for optional cosmetics) and has a great community.

You own a plot of land on which you build a house and crafters, place decorations and flowers, etc;
You become proficient in hunting, foraging, mining, fishing, bug catching, cooking, gardening, ranching (animal husbandry) and furniture making;
You interact and become friends with NPCs and some of them even have LIGHT romance options;
You EXPLORE the map and solve easy/medium puzzles;
All of the above are tied together by QUESTS and you will also interact with (and receive help from) the players.

I definitely recommend this game, but I must also tackle what I find bothering:
-the climbing mechanic is weird and frustrating on some surfaces;
-groves should be an individual or party resource, just like mining nodes;
-the game has an acceptable amount of grind when it comes to everything EXCEPT 'Makeshift is all mine', the oyster pebble and starred stones;
-co-op is not satisfying enough in its current state (the future shared housing update will be a great start).
